-- $2 Trillion May Be Needed for Global Issues, IMF Says
-- B y   A n d y   S h a r p
-- 2012-02-03T07:27:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/-2-trillion-may-be-needed-for-global-issues-imf-says-correct-.html
(Corrects to say world, not IMF, needs $2 trillion.)  The world may need a total of $2
trillion to cover all global economic eventualities,  Naoyuki
Shinohara , a deputy managing director at the  International
Monetary Fund , said today at a briefing in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
